%% Feast Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Operator as Feast Operator<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant FeastPod as Feature Server Pod<br/>(multi-container)
    participant Client as Client Application
    participant OnlineSvc as feast-{name}-online<br/>80 or 443/TCP
    participant Registry as Registry Server<br/>6570-6573/TCP
    participant DB as External DB<br/>(Postgres/Redis/etc.)
    participant CronPod as CronJob Pod<br/>(ose-cli)

    Note over User,FeastPod: Flow 1: FeatureStore Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply FeatureStore CR<br/>Auth: client cert/token
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Reconcile event<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Services,<br/>PVCs, ConfigMaps, RBAC, Routes<br/>HTTPS/TLS
    K8sAPI->>FeastPod: Schedule Pod

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 2: Online Feature Retrieval
    Client->>OnlineSvc: GET/POST features<br/>HTTP/HTTPS<br/>Auth: K8s RBAC / OIDC / None
    OnlineSvc->>Registry: Fetch metadata<br/>gRPC 6570/6571<br/>Optional TLS
    OnlineSvc->>DB: Read features<br/>Auth: Secret credentials
    DB-->>OnlineSvc: Feature data
    OnlineSvc-->>Client: Feature response

    Note over CronPod,FeastPod: Flow 3: CronJob Materialization
    Note right of CronPod: Scheduled by K8s CronJob
    CronPod->>K8sAPI: kubectl exec into Feast Pod<br/>HTTPS/TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>FeastPod: exec: feast apply /<br/>feast materialize-incremental
    FeastPod->>DB: Write materialized features
    DB-->>FeastPod: Confirmation

    Note over User,Operator: Flow 4: Notebook Integration
    User->>K8sAPI: Add feast label to Notebook CR
    K8sAPI->>Operator: NotebookConfigMap reconcile
    Operator->>K8sAPI: List FeatureStores,<br/>get client ConfigMaps
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create per-notebook ConfigMap
